# TypeScript and React Coding Standards

## General Guidelines

- Use TypeScript strict mode (enabled in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json))
- Use React 19 with JSX transform (no need to import React)
- Use Emotion CSS for styling with the `css` prop
- Follow the existing code style patterns

## Component Structure

- Use functional components with arrow function syntax
- Export components as named exports
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props when needed
- Keep components simple and focused

## Styling Patterns

- Use Emotion CSS with template literals
- Follow the existing styling patterns in [src/App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx)
- Use semantic class names and consistent spacing
- Prefer CSS-in-JS over external stylesheets

## Import/Export Patterns

- Use named imports/exports
- Import JSON files directly (as seen with content.json)
- Import constants from [src/constants.ts](mdc:src/constants.ts)

## Environment Variables

- Access environment variables through the constants file
- Use the REACT*APP* prefix for custom environment variables
- Handle undefined values gracefully with fallbacks
